definition.value: A nitroso compound that is carbaryl in which the amino hydrogen is substituted by a nitroso group.

An organosulfur compound that is a di-thiol adduct resulting from the reaction of the mycotoxin patulin with 4-bromothiophenol. Used in research into developing user-friendly and rapid immunoanalytical techniques for the decontamination by patulin in foodstuffs.
The dihydrochloride salt of ICR 340.
An organic heterotricyclic compound that is benzo[b][1,5]naphthyridine substituted by methoxy, chloro and {3-[(2-chloroethyl)(ethyl)amino]propyl}amino groups at positions 2, 7 and 10, respectively.

An organosulfur compound that is a di-thiol hapten resulting from the reaction of the mycotoxin patulin with 4-bromothiophenol followed by condensation of the resultant adduct with beta-alanine. Used in research into developing user-friendly and rapid immunoanalytical techniques for the decontamination by patulin in foodstuffs.
An ammonium ion that is ICR 340 (free base) in which the tertiary amino group and the nitrogen of the benzonaphthpyridine ring are protonated.

A glycotetraosylceramide having N-acetyl-beta-D-neuraminyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)-alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucose as the hexasaccharide component. It is overexpressed in some cancers and has been linked to disease progression.

A carbohydrazide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3,5-dinitrosalicylic acid  with one of the amino groups of hydrazine. It is a metabolite of nifursol found in foodstuffs of animal origin.

An eight amino acid peptide consisting of L-aspartic acid, L-tyrosine, L-lysine, four L-aspartic acid residues, and L-lysine joined in sequence by peptide linkages. It is widely used as a fusion tag for the purification and detection of a wide variety of recombinant proteins.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of ribavirin carboxylic acid arising from the deprotonation of the carboxy group. Major species at pH 7.3.
A  metal-oxygen cluster containing 1 calcium atom, 4 managanese atoms and 5 oxygen atoms. It is the catalytic center of water oxidation in photosystem II (PSII).
A pyrimidine deoxyribonucleotide(1-) residue obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of N(3)-methyl-2'-deoxycytosine 5'-monophosphate residue.
A zwitterionic group derived from N(1)-ethyl-2'-deoxyadenosine 5'-monophosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
Tetraanion of 3-hydroxyphenylacetyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of phosphate and diphosphate functions; major microspecies at pH 7.3
Tetraanion of 4-hydroxyphenylacetyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of phosphate and diphosphate functions; major microspecies at pH 7.3
Tetraanion of 3,4-dihydroxyphenylacetyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of phosphate and diphosphate functions; major microspecies at pH 7.3
A dihydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of (3,5-dihydroxyphenyl)acetic acid, arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group; major microspecies at pH 7.3.

Xanthan gum is a polysaccharide produced by the bacteria Xanthomonas campestris. It is composed of pentasaccharide repeat units, comprising two glucose units, two mannose units, and one glucuronic acid unit. Its main chain consists of beta-D-glucose units linked at the 1 and 4 positions. Trisaccharide side chains contain a D-glucuronic acid unit between two D-mannose units linked at the O-3 position of every other glucose residue in the main chain. Approximately one-half of the terminal D-mannose contains a pyruvic acid residue linked via keto group to the 4 and 6 positions, with an unknown distribution. D-Mannose unit linked to the main chain contains an acetyl group at position O-6.

A branched amino octasaccharide compound consisting of a beta-D-GlcNAc residue at the reducing end with a Man-alpha(1->3)-[Man-alpha(1->6)-Man-alpha(1->6)]-Man-beta(1->4)-GlcNAc moiety attached via a beta-(1->4)-linkage and two Fuc residues attached via alpha-(1->3)- and alpha-(1->6)-linkages.

A branched amino nonasaccharide derivative that is beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the mannosyl group is substituted at position 3 by a beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man group and at position 6 by an alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man group, while the GlcNAc residue at the reducing end also carries two Fuc residues attached via alpha-(1->3)- and alpha-(1->6)-linkages.
